The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems, specifically Hamiltonicity detection in undirected graphs and bipartite graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), and Graph Theory (cs.GT). Among these, cs.DM and cs.CC are the most likely categories, as the paper involves combinatorial and algorithmic techniques for solving a well-known NP-hard problem. The other categories are also possible, as the paper involves geometric and structural properties of graphs, as well as computational methods for evaluating determinants and counting cycle covers.
